Peru Stocks: Edegel, Ferreyros, IRL, Maple, Siderperu, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-04-28T01:33:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/peru-stocks-edegel-ferreyros-irl-maple-siderperu-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index rose 1.1 percent to 17,959.32. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed 0.3 percent to 2,461.11.  Industrial stocks rallied as investors speculated earnings
reports will be positive, said Daniel Romero, an analyst at
Lima-based investment fund NC&F Inversiones SA.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, jumped 7.5 percent to 72 cents.
 Empresa Siderurgica del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of Gerdau
SA known as Siderperu, rose 6.5 percent to 1.15 soles. Refineria
la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s Repsol YPF SA,
gained 3.9 percent to 1.34 soles. Edegel SA (EDEGELC1 PE), the
Peruvian unit of Spain’s Endesa SA, rose 3.3 percent to 1.55
soles.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor
for Caterpillar Inc., climbed 2.2 percent to 2.75 soles.  Precious metals miners gained after gold rose to a record
in New York.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals explorer with a
gold mine in Peru, rose 3.9 percent to $1.35. Soc. Minera El
Brocal SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a silver and zinc producer, advanced
2.8 percent to 37 soles. Volcan Cia Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE),
Peru’s largest silver producer, gained 2.7 percent to 2.65 soles.
Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s biggest
precious-metals miner which is scheduled to report earnings
tomorrow, rose 1.3 percent to $38.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  